post_text: With our summer cleaning and updating, I have been going through things in the coaches office and have found many old game films (some very old). I will be posting years and types of media over the next few days or weeks. If you are interested in any of the films, it will be first come, first serve. (First to pick them up at my house gets them!) I have old reel to reel film, DVD and smaller video cartridges. Obviously some of it will have to be converted to watch. What I post is all that I have. I hate to throw them away. I know my kids enjoy watching their games so I figured others may like to as well! Stay tuned if you are interested. I may be able to get to posting later today or tonight!

post_text: All incoming Freshman for the 2019-2020 school year wanting to participate in sports MUST set up an account on Arbiter Athlete to establish eligibility and other things for CHSAA. Please have your student log on to www.arbiterathlete.com. (It may come up as PlanetHS. That site will direct you to Arbiter Athlete.) They will need to sign up (not sign in). They will create an account using a few bits of information. Parents do not need to create an account and students do not need to link their account. Once they create an account, they may log out. I will do the rest of the work from there. If you have questions, you may comment here or call me. Please do this as soon as possible. It will only take a few minutes. Thank you!

Hello to everyone.

We have set the dates for the upcoming 2019 season.

$90 entry fee. $105 late registration.

This league is for kids that will be going into the 3rd-6th grades in the fall of 2019

Registration dates:

Sunday June 9 3pm-5pm
Saturday June 22 5pm-7pm
Saturday July 13 11am-1pm
Sunday July 21 4pm-7pm

We will set dates later for late registrations.

ABSOLUTELY NO REGISTRATIONS TAKEN AFTER FRIDAY JULY 26. NO EXCEPTIONS

You can go to spyfl.com to print out a registration form. We will also have forms at the registrations.

Registrations will be at the back of the Tiger Den at Sterling High School down Tiger Alley.

Sunday August 18 will be equipment checkout, coaches meeting and concussion training. This will be at Wally Post Gym at Sterling High School at the east doors.

12pm-2pm 5th/6th graders
2pm-4pm coaches meeting/concussion training
4pm-6pm 3rd/4th graders

Saturday September 7 will be the first day of games.

Please help spread the word.

The Lady Wildcats will be playing for 3rd place this afternoon at 2:00. Whether you are here watching or at home listening, the entire team and coaching staff would like to thank all of you for your support!! The dedication and hard work of these girls have been 2nd to none!! Basketball is a long season and it is hard work. Blood, sweat, tears, bruises, and sprains...we have had them all!! It has been an honor to be their coach and represent Fleming High School and community!! We would like to thank Mr. McCracken and Fleming School, Duane and Ramona Kirkwood, and Bob and Heather Tanner for providing meals for us while here at State. As well as all of the parents that provided food for us!! Thanks Carmen for driving us around and getting us there safely as well!!
Go Wildcats!!
ATTITUDE AND EFFORT!!

State tournament Information
Directions to CSU-P Massari Arena From Interstate 25, take Exit 101 to Highway 47 heading East. Take Bonforte Boulevard exit, then turn left (North) onto Bonforte Blvd. Parking is free but please adhere to the parking signs.

There is a no re-entry policy. IF you leave, you must purchase another ticket to get in.
Ticket Prices:
Great 8, Final 4, and Saturday Consolation
General Admission: $10.00
Students K-12 & Seniors (60+) $8.00
3rd/4th Place and Championship Sessions
General Admission: $11.00
Sudents K-12 & Seniors $8.00
All Session Passes (Available only online)
All Session Pass-Adult $50.00
All Session Pass-Students & Seniors $45.00
***Online ticket sales available vis GoFan.co (there is also a link on www.CHSAANow.com.
Morning sessions include 8:45 am, 10:15 am, 11:45 am and 1:15 pm games.
Afternoon sessions include 4:00 pm, 5:30 pm, 7:00 pm and 8:30 pm games.
The house will clear between sessions. (a separate ticket is needed for each session)

Entrances:
Spectators- Main Entrance Doors (West Side)

post_text: For any fans unable to attend the 1A Regional games in Brush on March 2-3, we will have live broadcasts available on the NFHS Network. A 30 day subscription is $9.99 and would include all of the games from this weekend. Our NFHS system is ran off the automated Pixellot system and shows time and score of each game and includes sounds from our announcers. It's decent option for those unable to attend or those wanting to watch later. It should be available under live events at Brush High School.

Clothes for my younger 2 as they lost everything. Quincy is a size 12 and size 4 shoes and my son Kanyon is a size 10 and size 3 shoes. Quincy is almost 9 and likes craftsy stuff, American girl dolls, drawing, and animals. Kanyon is 7 and a complete country kid and likes trucks, tractors, legos, farm and ranch stuff, and sports.

Also, Chris Green is taking donations for meals for the family that they can freeze and reheat. Post below if this is something you could help with and I will get you into contact with her.

We have set up registration dates and times for the 2017 season:

Sunday June 11 5pm-7pm

Saturday June 24 5pm-7pm

Saturday July 15 11am-2pm

Sunday July 23 4pm-7pm

Registration will be at the west side of the Tiger Den at Sterling High School down Tiger Alley. Registration forms can be filled out and downloaded at spyfl.com We will also have forms at registration.

*****REGISTRATION DEADLINE IS FRIDAY JULY 28*****
Absolutely no registrations will be taken after that. We will set up times that last week for late registrations. There is a late fee and times will be posted later.

Other important dates:

Equipment checkout will be Sunday August 20 at the east doors of Wally Post Gym at Sterling High School.
5th/6th grade 12pm-2pm
3rd/4th grade 4pm-6pm

Coaches meeting and concussion training will be 2pm-4pm.

Season will start Saturday September 9. Uniforms will also be given out at that time. Pictures will also be taken that day.

Help spread the word. We will post reminders as the dates get closer.

Thank you.

Fleming FBLA and FFA chapters are wanting to assist with the fire relief in Logan/Philips County Fire Relief in any way possible. At this time, we are collecting MONETARY donations in the front office. If you would like to send money with your child or bring money in yourself, there will be a collection jar in the front office until next Friday. Checks can be made out to Haxtun Chamber of Commerce with fire relief in the memo. Pennies, nickles, dimes.. any little bit will help the families and community get back on their feet!

We are only collecting money at this time. Clothing and other items can be taken to the Old Smith Hardware building in Haxtun.
